last_episode_to_air.name: What Lies Beneath
last_episode_to_air.overview: Kendra and her team decides to go rogue in their quest to discover the true cause of the ferry's sinking.

name: Departure
overview: Follow the mystery of Flight 716 - a passenger plane that vanishes over the Atlantic Ocean. Following the mysterious crash, recently widowed, brilliant aviation investigator Kendra Malley is called in to investigate by her former boss and mentor Howard Lawson.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: The high-octane conspiracy drama returns for a third season, focusing on the mysterious sinking of a sea ferry bound for Newfoundland, Canada. The investigation team, led by Kendra Malley and Dominic Hayes begin to unravel the many tangled threads of the investigation. The team must race to uncover the truth behind the disaster and help to heal the damage caused by the terrible tragedy.

tagline: The journey's over. The lies have just begun.

episodes.name: Vanished
episodes.overview: When TransOcean Flight 716 vanishes over the Atlantic Ocean with 256 people on board, crash investigator Kendra Malley is called in.

episodes.name: Survivor
episodes.overview: The hunt for wreckage continues as the TSIB team learn more about Donovan. Kendra wonders if the plane's lone survivor is hiding something.

episodes.name: Prime Suspect
episodes.overview: Madelyn’s memories of the crash provide the team with a lead, and a new witness comes forward with disturbing information about Donovan.

episodes.name: Sabotage
episodes.overview: Kendra tries to make sense of conflicting evidence and is stunned by the betrayal of someone close to her, while AJ puts his life in danger.

episodes.name: Grounded
episodes.overview: An unlikely source has proof of a conspiracy to cover up the truth about the crash, and the team scramble to recover the black boxes.

episodes.name: Endgame
episodes.overview: Kendra comes up with a plan to confront the Flight 716 conspirators and expose the cover up.

episodes.name: Runaway
episodes.overview: Kendra Malley is called to the U.S. to investigate a high-speed train crash in rural Michigan.

episodes.name: Fugitive
episodes.overview: Kendra learns about a mysterious passenger on the run after escaping from U.S. Marshals' custody.

episodes.name: Walk the Line
episodes.overview: Kendra shares information with her FBI counterpart; Kendra gets a big break in the case.

episodes.name: Wrecking Ball
episodes.overview: Kendra looks for connections between the victims; Max and Kendra hatch a plan with the FBI.

episodes.name: Don't Tread on Me
episodes.overview: Kendra and Agent Hunter find proof of a larger conspiracy; a confrontation leaves Kendra shaken.

episodes.name: Witness
episodes.overview: As the case winds down, Kendra feels there's still a missing piece of the puzzle.

episodes.name: The Tempest
episodes.overview: A night ferry crossing suddenly goes horribly wrong. Kendra Malley and her team are called in to investigate the sinking.

episodes.name: Dead in the Water
episodes.overview: Having found signs of life on board the sunken vessel, the race for recovery continues along with gathering of evidence. Survivors start experiencing flashbacks.

episodes.name: Stowaway
episodes.overview: Kendra Malley and her team continue to investigate the ferry sinking. The Captain's story comes into question, when a recovered video shows a different turn of events below deck, than was first told by survivors.

episodes.name: Devil and the Deep Blue Sea
episodes.overview: There is unexpected betrayal within the ranks, a possibly innocent man is arrested, and then a dead diver surfaces from the wreck.

episodes.name: Shot Across The Bow
episodes.overview: A diver's mysterious identity proves to be the key to Kendra's discovery that an ally has been sabotaging her investigation from the start.

episodes.name: What Lies Beneath
episodes.overview: Kendra and her team decides to go rogue in their quest to discover the true cause of the ferry's sinking.
